# Dynamic Multilingual Story Website

This project will build a highly polished, responsive, and interactive website to host a 10-page story by Ahmedin Jebal. The site will utilize a dynamic JavaScript architecture to seamlessly switch languages without page reloads.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> Please review the open questions below to clarify the requirements before we proceed with development.

## Proposed Changes

We will build the site using modern **Vanilla JavaScript, HTML, and CSS**, bundled with Vite for an optimal developer experience and optimized production build.

### Core Architecture

- **Project Foundation**: Vanilla JS + HTML + CSS (bundled with Vite for fast local development).
- **Languages**: Out-of-the-box support for **Amharic** and **Oromic**.
- **Data Management**: Story content stored in `content.json`. A dropdown will update text instantly without reloads.
- **Pagination**: We will use a **"Next / Previous" chapter format**. This looks highly professional, much like a Kindle or medium article, preventing the fatigue of scrolling a massive wall of text.
- **Author Presentation**: The very first page will act as a cover, featuring a beautifully framed section for the **author's photo** (Ahmedin Jebal), a title, and a brief intro.

---

### Design System and Aesthetics
> [!TIP]  
> We will aim for a **Premium Reading Experience**.

- **Typography**: Clean, highly legible fonts optimized for long-form reading (e.g., *Inter* or *Merriweather* for English, and suitable fonts for Amharic/Arabic if requested).
- **Theme**: We will implement a sleek UI with smooth gradients, soft shadows (glassmorphism), and a **Dark Mode / Light Mode** toggle, which is essential for reading.
- **Micro-animations**: Subtle hover effects, smooth chapter transitions, and elegant fading when switching languages.

### Components

#### [NEW] `index.html`
The main shell of the application containing the Navbar (Language Dropdown, Theme Toggle), the Reader Container, and Pagination Controls.

#### [NEW] `style.css`
Advanced custom CSS utilizing CSS Variables for theming, flexbox/grid for layout, and modern animations.

#### [NEW] `main.js`
The core logic for:
- Fetching and parsing the story JSON
- Handling the language switch
- Handling chapter navigation (Previous/Next)
- Toggling Light/Dark mode

#### [NEW] `content.json`
A structured JSON file that holds the 10 pages for each language.

## Verified Requirements

1. **Languages**: Amharic and Oromic.
2. **Text**: We will set up the structure and placeholders so you can paste the text yourself once ready.
3. **Pagination Choice**: Book-style "Next/Previous" buttons with an Author Cover page.

